# Open Courseware Lab Workflow

## Project Goal
- Build shareable multilingual interactive courseware across math/physics/chemistry.
- Keep each problem as an independent lesson page under taxonomy paths.

## Content Taxonomy (Required)
- Store lessons at: `lessons/<subject>/<grade>/<topic>/<problem-slug>/`
- Each lesson must include:
  - `index.html`
  - `meta.json`
  - local assets in `assets/`
- Use deploy-safe relative paths only (no local absolute filesystem paths).

## Metadata and Catalog (Required)
- Root homepage is a catalog page.
- Catalog data comes from `lessons/manifest.json` (not hardcoded cards).
- After adding/updating any `lessons/**/meta.json`, run:
  - `node ./scripts/generate-lessons-manifest.mjs`
- Ensure `lessons/manifest.json` is updated before release.

## Release Flow (Required)
- Use branch workflow: feature branch -> PR -> merge to `main`.
- Respect protected main branch (no direct force push).
- Deploy production from `main` with Cloudflare Pages:
  - `npx wrangler pages deploy . --project-name open-courseware-lab --branch main`

## QA Baseline Before Release
- Verify root catalog renders cards and links to target lesson paths.
- Verify lesson core interactions:
  - tab switching
  - teacher mode step reveal
  - language switch + auto-rotate
- Verify mobile behavior at least on 390px and 320px widths (no blocking overflow).
